comments[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-12T23:09:22.399Z",codex-pm-audit-extraction,"Decision evidence: live extension contracts expose registerFlags and command overrides; the existing pm-governance-audit package is the canonical package-first target. Chosen hybrid ownership, audit alias, --force bare-core fallback, and zero public audit SDK surface."
close_reason: "D1/D2 resolved: hybrid extension-owned commands/flags; audit alias; --force fallback; no public audit SDK surface."
body: "## Decision\n\nChoose the hybrid extension mechanism. `pm-governance-audit` owns the four audit commands and registers audit-only flags on existing core commands through `registerFlags`; package-owned handlers implement linked-artifact audit reports without keeping audit behavior in core. Add `audit` as a package alias so `pm install audit --project` resolves to the existing first-party package.\n\nBare core retains only generic ownership enforcement and accepts `--force` as the explicit fallback. No audit-named command, CLI flag, MCP parameter, completion, help entry, public SDK runner, or public SDK audit-bypass option remains in the default distribution. Internal generic enforcement values may remain only where they are not public audit API.\n\nThe four public audit runner exports are removed as an intentional breaking boundary change, coordinated with the first-party package minimum-version bump and changelog. This follows the user directive that the default CLI and SDK contain no audit functionality."
